# Sub-repo manifest

Index of registered sub-repos in this company's stack. Authoritative
— the orchestrator consults this file to know what to query, what to
write notices into, and which depth file to read for each.

Update via `/register` or by editing this file directly.

> **The index, not the depth.** Each entry below is metadata only.
> Per-sub-repo accumulated state lives at
> [`state/sub-repos/<name>.md`](../../state/sub-repos/) — that's
> where current branch, HEAD, advertisement, and references to all
> orchestrator artifacts touching the repo live.

## Format

```
## <name>
- **Role:** api | ios | web | devops | other
- **Local path:** /absolute/path/to/repo
- **Git remote:** <url>
- **Default branch:** main
- **Kit-enabled:** true | false | unknown
- **Registered:** YYYY-MM-DD
- **Last synced HEAD:** <sha or "never">
- **Last synced at:** YYYY-MM-DD or "never"
- **State file:** [state/sub-repos/<name>.md](state/sub-repos/<name>.md)
- **Notes:** <one-line — anything that affects how state is queried>
```

**Kit-enabled detection:** `true` if `<local-path>/.claude/foundation.json`
exists with `kit.repo` containing `claude-kit`. `false` if it doesn't.
`unknown` only during the moment between registration and the first
`/sync-check`.

